Exposing my secrets 💕 I’m an extreme nail biter lol skin and all. It’s so embarrassing. Here’s a look at how I save money and achieve beautiful nails at home 🌻 special thanks to @kissproducts for the lovely gifts. 

- Step 1: select the nail size 
- Step 2: dehydrate nail with alcohol and buff/file your natural nail
- Step 3: apply a small dot of glue in the center of the nail. *do not over saturate with glue as bubbles will appear and cause the nail to lift over time. 
- Step 4: apply the nail and maintain pressure for at least 20 seconds
- Step 5: moisturize your cuticles 

*avoid water for at least 3/4 hours 

Enjoy 🌻 Hope this helps. If you’re a nail biter like me lol your secrets are safe with me. Save your money 🤍

The biggest joke of the year has been the prices at the nail salons. Press on nails have been my go to for months, and I don’t see how I wasn’t here sooner. Special thanks to @kissproducts for always staying on top of the trends and upgrading the glue to max hold 🤣💕 LOVE YALL! 

Here’s how I get it done: 

1. Prep nail (buff/clip/file)
2. Clip cuticle/hang nails
3. Dehydrate the nail (Alcohol in spray bottle) 
4. Find the right size nails before you begin 
5. Small dot of glue in the center of the nail
6. Press the nail down and place it as close to the natural cuticle as possible. 
7. Apply nail treatment (oil/lotion)
8. Avoid water/hand washing for 1 hour 

Happy nail days 💅🏾 from me to you 🌻

One of the critical reasons your hair is “not growing” or retaining length is failure to maintain trims. 

The recommended trim schedule that I follow is about every 6-8 weeks. Since I’m normally wearing protective styles, I tend to get a trim closer to the 8 week mark. Aside from using the products that work well on your hair texture and density, always always always include a trim. 
Your hair will love you for it 💕

Follow and share for more tips like these 🥰 special thanks to @roxeedenise for keeping me on track especially after my last micro link disaster lol but I’ll update you guys on that in a few. ✨ 

find a licensed professional that you trust to assist you on your hair journey. Thanks @roxeedenise 😘🌻

Side bar: straight, sleek, and long hair is not my goal— healthy hair is. 🙌🏾

I got so many questions on my story when I posted about the SouthWest Wanna Get Away flights. Here are the details: 

I usually do my research before booking traveling plans, but Southwest has the most consistently reliable affordable fares. 🙌🏾

Southwest Wanna Get Away fares offer travelers an opportunity to save on travel costs. Southwest has no change or cancellation fees, and every passenger can check two bags for free.

The main differences between Wanna Get Away and Anytime fares is refundability and points earning rates. While Wanna Get Away fares can be refunded as future travel funds, Anytime fares are refunded as cash back.

Happy traveling ✨🌻

A premium manicure brought to you by @kissproducts 
Style: Gorgeous 

FAQS + Answers 🌻 

1. How long do they last? Up to 2 weeks (however the results may vary)

2. How do you get them to last longer? Buff & dehydrate the nail before application of nail glue. Avoid water for at least 1 hour at least!!!!

3. How much glue should I use? Less is more! Use a drop size amount in the center of the nail. Press and hold 20s until the glue spreads evenly. 

Family the results will vary based on your daily routines. These are my personal experiences. ✨ I hope they help and save you a fortune in the meantime.
